      "body": "**T5 opening Ground: gate PASSED, but \"close the 9 sorries\" is over-optimistic \u2014 extraction is the real deliverable.**\n\n**Good news \u2014 STEP 0 gate PASSED.** The `Picard/IdentityComponent` import cone (9 AJC modules + Mathlib) contains **no \u010cech/flat-base-change engine**, so the extraction runs safely in parallel with the live T2 FBC build. Details in the `AJC.picrep` roadmap comment and `recommendation.md`.\n\n**Caveat \u2014 STEP 2 (\"close the 9 structural sorries\") is mostly not achievable this run.** Ground checked all 9:\n- **\u00a71 group-scheme substrate (4 sorries)** is blocked on a genuine Mathlib gap: \"connected + `k`-rational section \u27f9 geometrically connected\" (Stacks 037Q/04KU) and descent-of-clopen (02LB/04KS). Confirmed absent from v4.31 `Geometrically/Connected.lean`.\n- **Pic\u2070-specific leaves (5 sorries)** inherit the **sorry-backed FGA foundation** (`PicScheme` / `GrpObj (PicScheme C)` are `\u27e8sorry\u27e9` in `FGAPicRepresentability.lean`), so they cannot close axiom-clean until FGA representability lands. `degree` also needs \u03c7-blocked Hilbert-poly; `isAbelianVariety` / `finrank_eq_genus` overlap the separate active `AJC.pic0av` tangent-space cone.\n\n**Realistic T5 deliverable:** the **isolated green subproject** `SubProjects/Picard-IdentityComponent` (build-isolation for parallel iteration), 9 sorries preserved as documented placeholders. At most one marginal structural tidy (`Pic0Scheme` def, if `LocallyOfFiniteType (PicScheme C).hom` resolves). For net picrep sorry closures, higher-leverage work is a session on **FGA representability** or the **037Q/04KU descent substrate**, not IdentityComponent.\n\n**Minor, unrelated:** `horizon` warns `MR0555258-Compactifying-Picard` is pinned to mathlib `v4.30.0` while `external_libraries` declares `v4.31.0` \u2014 relevant to T7; worth a toolchain-align check before that run.",
